{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "electronic_circuit_copper_cable_lost_at_chain_head",
  "notes": "BUG: topology_boundaries misses the chain-head case where a FREE belt has no belt feeder (fed by an inserter from a machine output). In this layout the copper-cable feeder chain is a single West-facing belt at (4,7) delivering to the trunk at (3,7); it is fed by an inserter from a copper-cable machine above/below. When the SAT bbox grows to absorb (4,7), physical_feeder_hit returns None and no perimeter-IN boundary is emitted. SAT solves without the input constraint and produces a layout that drops copper-cable entirely \u2014 (3,7) gets repurposed for copper-plate and (4,7) is removed. No walker veto fires because routed_paths continuity checks only existing routed paths; a missing input is invisible. Repro URL: http://localhost:5173/?item=electronic-circuit&rate=10&machine=assembling-machine-1&in=iron-plate%2Ccopper-plate%2Csteel-plate%2Cstone%2Ccoal%2Cwater%2Ccrude-oil%2Ciron-ore%2Ccopper-ore",
